com.giannoules.proxstor.connection

Class ProxStorConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.giannoules.proxstor.connection.ProxStorConnector

  • public class ProxStorConnector
extends Object
    Provides client application interface into a ProxStor instance. Capabilities exposed here includes management of:
    • Users
    • Devices
    • Locations
    • Environmental
    Note that instantiation of back-end Graph instance is not provided. That must be done outside this connector.

      • ProxStorConnector

        public ProxStorConnector(String path)
        Instantiate ProxStorConnector and initiate a connection to a specified ProxStor instance. It is recommended to reuse a single ProxStorConnector for resource leveraging purposes.
        Parameters:
        path - URI connection string to ProxStor. Example: "http://localhost:8080/proxstor-webapp/api"

      • addUserKnows

        public boolean addUserKnows(User u,
                   User v,
                   int strength)
        establish a user knows relationship between two users. the strength of the relationship must be specified. User u --- knows {strength: strength} ---> User v
        Parameters:
        u - the user who knows the other user
        v - the user who is known by the other user
        strength - the strength of the knows relationship. valid values [1..100].
        Returns:
        true if the relationship is established; false otherwise

      • updateUserKnows

        public boolean updateUserKnows(User u,
                      User v,
                      int strength)
        update the knows relationship strength between users. a previous knows must have been established from User u to User v.
        Parameters:
        u - the user who knows the other user
        v - the user who is known by the other user
        strength - the new strength the knows relationship. valid values [1..100].
        Returns:
        true if the relationship is updated; false otherwise

      • deleteKnows

        public boolean deleteKnows(User u,
                  User v)
        remove the knows relationship strength between users. a previous knows must have been established from User u to User v.
        Parameters:
        u - the user who knows the other user
        v - the user who is known by the other user
        Returns:
        true if the relationship is removed; false otherwise
